					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That's quite esoteric. I suppose one could add a value for it, as long as it does not turn the whole proposal into a complete joke.<br /><br />On another note, there already exist ROM images with 64 MiB and more in PRG-ROM size --- two OneBus plug-and-plays with exactly 64 MiB, and that &quot;Coolgirl 320-in-1&quot; multicart which has more than 64 MiB of PRG-ROM (and an <a href="https://clusterrr.com/temp/coolgirl.cpp" class="postlink">insanely complex mapper</a>). NES 2.0 only allows up to 64 MiB at the moment, and 64 MiB are implicitly represented by zero PRG-ROM banks.</div>

