				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Just a wild guess, but Nintendo's factory probably tested 2A03 CPUs received from Ricoh, and the test rig had a 2A03 socket and some additional MMIO port that controls the test mode pin, letting the program switch between test mode and run mode. But I imagine that sort of stuff would be even more obscure than the Nintendo PlayStation. So until such a test rig surfaces, I oppose baking into NES 2.0 a means to distribute a firmware for it.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

